caption: Placed a huge order online at 10:45am for a work meeting, with scheduled pick up an hour later. It was all hot, ready, and correct!

Very disappointing! Put in an order online for pickup and was told the wait was 50 minutes. I showed up an hour later and still had to wait 15 minutes for my food to come out.  The food was average to bad. We tried a mix of different things because it didn't seem like there was a specialty.  Sushi was OK. Spring rolls were fine. The chicken teriyaki was just a barely seasoned and dry chicken breast instead of the marinated skewers shown in the photo on the website. Like something disappointing I would throw together myself on a Tuesday night. Egg drop soup tasted of nothing and the miso tasted like dishwaster. Fried rice was pretty good though!  It's entirely possible we just ordered the wrong things. Or maybe they had an off night. But my guess is the menu is just too big for them to turn out things consistently well. I'll stick to restaurants that focus executing one cuisine well moving forward.

T he sunomono at the Grubb Rd location has thinly sliced cucumber and lots of seafood, the way it should be.  Called the restaurant and they told me to call Postmates. Postmates has yet to get back to me. Honestly, the most disappointing meal EVER. I will never order from the Colesville Rd location again. Never. The Grubb Rd location has our business forever. I was across the street dropping off a UPS package and thought I would pick up dinner for my wife who is Asian. I do this often at many Asian restaurants in the area. Since she is on a Veggie kick lately I ordered Vegetable lo-main and Hot & Sour Soup. It was about 6pm and they only had a few tables with people. The service was fast and it came out fast, but for Vegetable... Lo-main she had to cook her own veggies since there were little to none in it and I have to agree. I am not one to write a review and after reading these, they may put out good Sushi and others may like it but give me a salad or McDonald's and I am happy, but I normally only get food for her. She said the Hot and Sour was to spicy but I will say that is probably her, but Vegetable Lo-Main should be Lo-main Vegetable since it was 98% noodles. I may not care about food that much and easily pleased with most food, But I do know what it should be and what it should not. I can honestly say I know restaurants and have been in more than most people since I have been a restaurant equipment dealer for 30 years and now a manufactures representative for factories that make food service equipment.  I have built many restaurants in this area and sold equipment to restaurants all over the world. I will say the layout is not bad, it seemed clean, prices average but portions from what I can tell are weak. If I had read these reviews before tonight, I would not have known what to say except it seems like most are there for Sushi. I doubt she will go there now and I know I will not go back. I know in this business you have to be consistent. I did say the prices were average but not for .30 cents worth of noodles. Next week I will be in Orlando FL for the NAFEM show. That is the Largest Food Equipment Show there is and people come from all over the world. They do give samples of all kinds of food there demonstrating there equipment and how great the food is being cooked on there equipment, so she always enjoys this show.

Best place ever. Love everything about here..
One of the best sushi shops in the NCR...very clean, great food!..courteous staff and the price is just right!

Some of the best sushi I have had.

Family enjoys this 4 Corners gem!

I love their sushi!
It's one of our neighborhood restaurants. The staff is courteous, the place is clean and the food is flavorful. The sushi is well prepared and they offer a creative variety of rolls.
Great food and service! Been coming here for years!
Easy to get to...parking available...considerate service and tasty food.

You know that any place serving two kinds of cuisine is going to suffer from "master of none" syndrome. So it goes here. Stick with the Thai - hard to go wrong with that. But it's uninspired, so patronize if you're in the area, but if you're looking for an experience, head to Silver Spring or Wheaton where the offerings are more substantial.
We love this restaurant, great food, very friendly staff and ample parking.
Went here for a nice sushi lunch with my daughter. Great service and delicious sushi!
The drunken noodles served with broccoli in sauteed garlic sauce and wonton soup is my go to meal......very yummy🤗
Great food and service at fair prices.
Service isn't stellar....but the food is fantastic m

My friends have been dining here for years and I finally had time to stop by and try their sushi. We ordered everything from salmon, shrimp tempura, snow crab rolls. I had the chirashi which had plenty of fish but they did include imitation crab meat and egg. Not a huge fan at all. Overall food is decent and reasonably price. I'll be back to try some of their other entries. Restaurant had wide open concept with plenty of seating for parties of 4-6 people.

Love their Crispy Shredded Beef. Have come back many times for this dish. Very nice atmosphere. Fast/friendly staff, and very reasonable prices.  That said - tried getting takeout. The "crispy" beef would have been better described as soggy.
The food is good. The variety, proximity and appeal to my whole family makes this place five stars. We LOVE the Tom Yum, crispy beef and American Dream roll.

Great lunch specials. Never seen it crowded. Kids from the school across the street tend to get distracted by other nearby offerings. The sashimi is exceptional, the nigiri is what you'd expect, and the special rolls have never disappointed me or my relatives.
Great food, the best for lunch sub $10. Quick service

The food variety is great and everything I've had has been made well. Prices are very reasonable. The service has always been prompt, knowledgeable, and polite. The bar area is comfortable and nice for a drink and or quick date. The dining area is also comfortable and the lighting is complimentary.
Great food!
Restaurant atmosphere is pleasant and inviting. Food is always very good and the staff are very friendly and helpful. Parking is a bit of a hassle sometimes though but that is not a deterrent.

The sushi, especially the specialty rolls, is well crafted and thought out. Noise level typically hovers around around a lively buzz. Prices are comfortable for the area, and clearly fund the high quality service as well as the high quality food.
Good food, clean environment and nice mixture of patrons.

One of my favorites by far. Sushi is always fresh and creatively done! I really really enjoy this place. I think they could add a better bar menu, but apart from that this will be "must go" place for me.
Parking was around the back! Sushi was okay
I was dinning alone and ate at the sushi bar. Great experience! Sushi was amazing and very fresh. Perfect fish to rice ratio for how sushi is supposed to be done. I will visit this place again.

Their sushi is on point...always made well and tastes fresh. The other main courses are average. I usually always get their sushi and I really enjoy the variety and creativity of their sushi dishes. Staff members are rather drab...you get the idea that they don't want to work there or that maybe there are having a bad day. Luckily, I take out most of the time so it doesn't affect me too much.
Different from most restaurants give it a shot!
This is a fairly good place for Silver spring residents. Fairly prices with good Thai flavor. Their Sushi variety is awesome too.

Last night, we parked, went in to eat, and were towed from the lot before our drink order arrived, a whopping six minutes of being on premises in total. Love the sushi, and the entrees are pretty good - but go for the sushi!
Sushi was fine but chinese was terrible and flavorless. 1 star for sushi and 1 for the cocktail.
Dinner bento boxes! Recently service has declined, but the rolls and boxes are pretty good.

Went on a Monday afternoon for lunch. Service and Ambience were fine. Lunch specials were definitely worth it, especially the sushi rolls; at 3 rolls (18 pcs) for around $10-$11 it was a steal.  Apps: Hot & Sour, Miso Soup, Kani Salad were all good.  Sushi: Nigiri options were super delicious; had the Mackerel, Eel, Salmon, White Tuna, and Tuna  Overall, I'd definitely go back again soon. Decent service, great sushi.

Always getting take out- good food- great atmosphere- wish We could eat there more.  It is really too bad there are not more nicer restaurants in this shopping center like RM.  12/2015:  Editing My review- the food seems to have gone a bit downhill over the last 6 months for some reason.  We will still eat here- just so they don't close.  I'm not sure what the problem is- but they need to figure out what is wrong in the kitchen.  I usually get some sushi (always OK- not too exciting)  & the Gen. Tso Shrimp.  Taste & texture have been way off from when they opened.  I hope they clean it up.  This is a great restaurant to have in the neighborhood and I hope their business is doing well.

There's two things I come here for, the sushi and the general tso.  Sushi is great and the prices are very fair.  There are tons of different rolls from simple to specialty rolls.  The general tso is one of my favorites, hot and extra crispy. So good lol. The staff is nice and you can tell people like this place because there's normally a wait to get seated.  Only downside is that they don't deliver lol, but you can't really criticize them for that.  Carry out is available though.
Excellent sushi rolls.
Great sushi!
Great food, good staff.  I've enjoyed everything I've ordered.  When there for lunch--on Saturdays, ask for the lunch menu.  And try the spicy tuna handrolls!
All the food was amazing and just the overall experience was great.

A nice addition to the Woodmore area which is critically short of good eats. We have been going to the Red Maple for about a year and each time the food seems to get better as they find their way. Funny thing is that we are not sushi fans but have taken to ordering some each time we dine there. And, each time it has been delicious. Overall the food is very good and getting better including some fine salads-a nice trend to see in a restaurant.
great food but rude server (guy with glasses), manager didn't care when I complained  either.
One of my favorite places! Staff is attentive, and not only is the food delicious, but also consistent!

Great sushi. So far I have tried the Black Pearl Roll, Tuna Amazing Roll, and Rainbow Roll (Rainbow Rolls are like my control variable for new sushi spots. If a restaurant manages to mess that up, I won't try anything else on the sushi menu). Will definitely return to try other items on the menu
